Here's how you would implement the same function in Lua:

```lua
function reverse_string(s)
    -- Initialize empty string
    result = ''

    -- Traverse through the string, append each character to the beginning of the result
    for i in string.gmatch(s, ".") do
        result = i .. result
    end
    return result
end

print(reverse_string('#$@!abcd1234'))  
print(reverse_string('*$&acd321@'))
```

Lua doesn't have a built-in syntax for iterating over individual characters of a string, so `string.gmatch(s, ".")` is used, which returns an iterator producing the individual characters.
