I see an error in my WordPress memory. Can you please help me, How can I fix this memory issue? The error displays a message like the one below:

Fatal error: Allowed memory size of 33554432 bytes exhausted (tried to allocate 2348617 bytes) in /home/username/public_html/site1/wp-includes/plugin.php on line xxx


How can I fix this memory issue ?
Thank You
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sure, the error you are seeing is due to PHP running out of memory. To increase the PHP memory limit, you have a few options:

Option 1: Edit your wp-config.php file
Add the following line to your wp-config.php file:

```php
define('WP_MEMORY_LIMIT', '256M');
```
This code tells WordPress to increase the PHP memory limit to 256MB.

Option 2: Edit your PHP.ini file
If you have access to your PHP.ini file, change the line in PHP.ini
Find this line in the PHP.ini file:

```
memory_limit = 32M 
```
and change it to:

```ini
memory_limit = 256M
```

Option 3: Edit your .htaccess file

Add the following line to your .htaccess file:

```htaccess
php_value memory_limit 256M
```

Note: It's always good to check with your hosting provider to understand your existing PHP memory limits and appropriate allocations. They should be able to assist you in increasing it. 

After making this change, you'll want to save your changes and then restart your web server to make sure the changes take effect. 

Remember, you should base your maximum memory limit based on your own server's capacity. If your server doesn't have enough physical memory, it could crash or get very slow. 

If none of these solutions work, it's a strong indication that something else might be wrong - for instance, a poorly coded plugin or theme could be causing the problem. It may be beneficial to disable plugins one by one to see if the issue gets resolved. 

Be sure to backup your site before making any changes in case anything goes wrong! You can use a plugin such as UpdraftPlus WordPress Backup Plugin, or manually backup from cPanel.
<|end|>


