Write a code in Python to reciprocate all the occurrences of a given value (10) with its square (100) in a dictionary.
dict = {1:10, 2:20, 3:30, 10:40, 5:50}
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sure, Here is a simple python script that will fulfill this requirement:

```python
# Original Dictionary
dictionary = {1:10, 2:20, 3:30, 10:40, 5:50}
print("Original Dictionary: ")
print(dictionary)

# Value we want to reciprocate all occurrence of
value_to_replace = 10

# Value to replace with
new_value = value_to_replace**2

# Create new Dictionary
new_dictionary = {key: (new_value if value == value_to_replace else value) for key, value in dictionary.items()}

print("Updated Dictionary: ")
print(new_dictionary)
```

When you run this script, any occurrence of the value 10 in the dictionary will be replaced with 100. In the resulting dictionary, you should have:
{1: 100, 2: 20, 3: 30, 10: 40, 5: 50}
