Create a JavaScript code to find the frequency of each character in a string, considering case sensitivity and ignoring special characters.
string="Java$Script#123"
<|end|>
<|asst|>
The below JavaScript code helps to find the frequency of each character in a string, considering case sensitivity, ignoring special characters and numbers. It uses a simple for loop to traverse the string and check every character.

```javascript
function characterFrequency(str) {
    let count = {};
    str = str.replace(/[^A-Za-z]/g, '');  // this will ignore special characters and numbers
    for(let i = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
        let char = str[i];
        if(count[char]) {
            count[char]++;
        } else {
            count[char] = 1;
        }
    }
    return count;
}

let string = "Java$Script#123";
console.log(characterFrequency(string));
```

When you run this code, you’ll see that it prints out an object that shows the frequency of each character in the string. It looks like this:

```
{
  J: 1,
  a: 2,
  v: 1,
  S: 1,
  c: 1,
  r: 1,
  i: 1,
  p: 1,
  t: 1
}
```

As you can see, this code correctly states that the character 'J' appears 1 time, 'a' appears 2 times, 'v' appears 1 time and so on. The special characters and numbers are ignored using regular expression.
