In Java, you can use the following code to remove all the trailing zeros from a long:

```java
public class Main{
    public static void main(String []args){
        long num = 450000000;
        while (num % 10 == 0) {
            num /= 10;
        }
        System.out.println(num);
    }
}
```

This code continuously divides the number by 10 as long as the last digit is zero. This effectively drops the trailing zero in each iteration. 

Please note that this modifying `long` as `int` will fail for any number greater than `Integer.MAX_VALUE` or less than `Integer.MIN_VALUE`. So, if you are using huge numbers then you should handle or consider overflow/underflow situations based on your use case.
