Construct a Java program that calculates the sum of the first 10 elements in the Fibonacci sequence, incorporating iterative algorithm for generating the series, variables for storage and control, and methods for computation.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here's a simple Java program that accomplishes the task:

```java
public class FibonacciSum {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int sum = fibonacciSum(10);
        System.out.println("The sum of the first 10 elements in the Fibonacci sequence is " + sum + ".");
    }

    public static int fibonacciSum(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return 0;
        }

        int fiboOne = 0;
        int fiboTwo = 1;
        int fiboSum = 1;
        int sum = 1;  // As first two elements are already considered in sum

        for (int i = 3; i <= n; i++) {
            fiboSum = fiboOne + fiboTwo;
            sum += fiboSum;
            fiboOne = fiboTwo;
            fiboTwo = fiboSum;
        }

        return sum;
    }
}
```
This program uses an iterative algorithm to generate the Fibonacci sequence. The `fibonacciSum` method takes an integer argument, `n`, and returns the sum of the first `n` Fibonacci numbers. The `main` method invokes this method and then outputs the sum.
<|end|>


