Project Name: CrossGraphic - Cross Platform GPU Management Tool

Functional Components:

1) GPU and OS Detection:
The CrossGraphic software should have a detector engine capable of identifying the type of GPU and its generation as well as the desktop operating system when launched. This information should be displayed, and the user should have an option to refresh or manually override the data.

2) Compatibility Management:
CrossGraphic should dynamically manage OpenGL, Metal, DirectX, Vulkan compatibility issues with different GPUs and desktop operating systems. If any compatibility issue arises, it should notify the user and automatically provide a solution to fix the issue if possible.

3) Version Control:
The solution should detect and manage different versions of OpenGL, Metal, DirectX, Vulkan, and provide a mechanism to update or downgrade an application’s required version according to the system’s compatibility.

4) Performance Report:
Performance metrics such as frame rate, memory usage, CPU and GPU usage should be generated for OpenGL, Metal, DirectX, and Vulkan based applications. It should provide an intuitive dashboard to monitor and analyze these metrics in real time.

5) Performance Enhancement:
Based on system status, application’s resources, and performance metrics, CrossGraphic should provide suggestions to improve the performance of applications.

6) Simulation and Testing Environment:
CrossGraphic should simulate different GPU, CPU, OS, and network environments to analyze the performance and compatibility of any graphics-based applications. A dedicated module should be provided to configure and manage all the parameters involved in the simulation.

7) Prediction Engine:
By leveraging machine learning algorithms, the system should analyze past and present trends to predict the behavior and performance of future GPUs and OS.

8) Network Compatibility and Management:
CrossGraphic should be capable of managing network dependent apps too. It should be able to detect and manage different versions of TCP and UDP protocols. If issues are found, it should update or downgrade these versions to prevent any network conflicts.

9) User Interface:
CrossGraphic should provide an intuitive and user-friendly interface for managing the simulations, interpreting the results, viewing reports, and following performance optimization recommendations, as well as managing all the other functionalities.
  
Technology Stack:
- C++ for core functionality and performance-driven tasks
- Qt for cross-platform desktop application development
- OpenGL for rendering graphics
- OpenCL for handling the computing tasks
- TensorFlow for the prediction engine
- TensorFlow for the prediction engine
- Wireshark for network protocol analysis and conflict management
- Jenkins for continuous integration and continuous delivery tasks.
