Bias in machine learning models can severely harm a model's accuracy. This can occur in various stages. One way to tackle this is to ensure that the data is well distributed over different classes. When splitting the data into training and testing sets, make sure that you have a good mix of different classes in both sets. 

It is also worth mentioning that since users' search terms are often sensitive information (even after anonymization), using them as labels to train an ML model may have potential ethical and legal concerns.
