What's the best way to asynchronously load an BitmapImage in C# using WPF?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here's an example of how you might asynchronously load a Bitmap Image in C# using WPF. This uses the `BitmapImage` class' ability to load resources from a URI asynchronously, in combination with the Dispatcher and the Task Parallel Library to keep your UI responsive:

```csharp
private async void LoadImageAsync(string imageUrl)
{
    await Task.Run(() => 
    {
        Dispatcher.Invoke(() =>
        {
            var bitmap = new BitmapImage();
            bitmap.BeginInit();
            bitmap.UriSource = new Uri(imageUrl, UriKind.RelativeOrAbsolute);
            bitmap.CacheOption = BitmapCacheOption.OnLoad;
            bitmap.CreateOptions = BitmapCreateOptions.IgnoreImageCache;
            bitmap.DecodePixelWidth = 200; // Adjust the number to change the size
            bitmap.EndInit();
            bitmap.Freeze(); // This is necessary otherwise you'll get an exception
            //When you try to set the source of the Image Control
            myImageControl.Source = bitmap;
        });
    });
}
```

The `BitmapImage` is set up to load the image from the provided URL asynchronously. It's also set up to cache the image on load and to ignore any previously cached images. The image is then frozen to make it cross-thread safe, and assigned to an Image control named `myImageControl`.

To use this method, simply call it with the URL of the image you'd like to load:

```csharp
LoadImageAsync("https://example.com/path/to/your/image.jpg");
```

Keep in mind your Image source should be loaded from Url otherwise if the image is in local resources you do not need to asynchronously load it.
<|end|>


