I want to know if matplotlib event handling even work with inline backend?
I am trying to plot an interactive plot with mouse click event but it is not working with matplotlib inline backend. But it works with qt backend.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
No, inline backend in matplotlib doesn't support interactive features. The inline backend is used in Jupyter notebooks to embed static images of the plot in the notebook. 

If you want to use interactive features in Jupyter notebooks, try using the `%matplotlib notebook` backend instead. If you want to use an external window, you can use `%matplotlib qt` if you have the PyQt package installed.

So, for Jupyter notebooks, it would look something like this:

```python
%matplotlib notebook
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
```

Note: `%matplotlib notebook` will create interactive plots embedded within the notebook. However, it may be a bit slower than `%matplotlib inline` because of the extra interactivity functionalities.
<|end|>


