Create a PHP program that fetches data from an SQL database and outputs the result in HTML page.
Not Applicable
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a simple PHP program that does that:

```PHP
<?php
//connect to the database
$host = 'localhost';
$db   = 'test_db';
$user = 'root';
$pass = '';
$charset = 'utf8mb4';

$dsn = "mysql:host=$host;dbname=$db;charset=$charset";
$opt = [
    PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE            => PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION,
    PDO::ATTR_DEFAULT_FETCH_MODE => PDO::FETCH_ASSOC,
    PDO::ATTR_EMULATE_PREPARES   => false,
];
$pdo = new PDO($dsn, $user, $pass, $opt);

//prepare and execute the query
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT * FROM users');
$stmt->execute();

$results = $stmt->fetchAll();

//output the results in a html page
echo "<html>";
echo "<body>";
echo "<table border='1'>";

echo "<tr>";
echo "<th>Id</th>";
echo "<th>Name</th>";
echo "<th>Email</th>";
echo "</tr>";

foreach ($results as $row) {
    echo "<tr>";
    echo "<td>" . $row['id'] . "</td>";
    echo "<td>" . $row['name'] . "</td>";
    echo "<td>" . $row['email'] . "</td>";
    echo "</tr>";
}

echo "</table>";
echo "</body>";
echo "</html>";
?>
```

This program assumes that you have a database named 'test_db' running on a local MySQL server (localhost), and inside this database there's a table named 'users' with fields 'id', 'name', 'email'. Also, it's assumed that the MySQL server's root user has no password.

PLEASE NOTE: This program has no error checking or exception handling. A real-world program would need to be much more robust and would need to protect against SQL injection attacks. The root user should also never be used in production!
<|end|>


