I have a multiple Rmd files (with writings) that I want to export into one pdf file. I did:

bookdown::render_book(input = "references/bookdown")


where my Rmd files were all in the input folders. The `output.yml` file contains:

bookdown::pdf_document2:
  toc: true
  toc_float: true


This successfully exports a pdf file, but depends on the page, the page number sometimes appear on the bottom or on either top left / right.
I tried:

bookdown::pdf_document2:
  includes:
    in-header:
      - \usepackage{fancyhdr}
      - \pagestyle{fancy}
      - \fancyfoot[C]{\thepage}
  toc: true
  toc_float: true


but did not make any difference.
Is it possible to keep the location of the page number in each page consistent?
