<|asst|>
Some sections (like the Table of Contents or the references) often switch to a different pagestyle (sometimes called 'plain'), which is possibly why your page numbers are behaving inconsistently. You might want to try to redefine the 'plain' pagestyle as well as the 'fancy' one, to make the 'plain' pagestyle copy the characteristics of the 'fancy' one.

You can do that by adding the following code in your in-header field:

```yaml
bookdown::pdf_document2:
  includes:
    in-header:
      - \usepackage{fancyhdr}
      - \pagestyle{fancy}
      - \fancyfoot[C]{\thepage}
      - \fancypagestyle{plain}{
          - \fancyhf{}
          - \fancyfoot[C]{\thepage}
        }
  toc: true
  toc_float: true
```

Also, ensure `- \usepackage{fancyhdr}` is written only once because it is a LaTeX package and should be included only once at the beginning of the document. Only the settings (like `\pagestyle{fancy}`, `\fancyfoot[C]{\thepage}`) should be used multiple times - for different page styles.

Remember to Indent your YAML properly as it could also influence the rendering of your document.
<|end|>


