- The table and each cell (td) have a border of 1px to clearly illustrate the divisions.
- The first row contains three cells, these are the "horizontal" divisions extended three times. The following five rows form the "vertical" divisions.
- The `width:33.33%` attribute provides equal width to the three horizontal divisions.
- The `height:20%` attribute gives equal height to each of the six vertical divisions.
