Create a Java program to sort an array of integers from the biggest to the smallest.
[2, 3, 8, 6, 1]
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a simple Java program that uses the Arrays sort function and a Collections reverse function to sort the array from biggest to smallest:

```java
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.Collections;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Integer[] numbers = {2, 3, 8, 6, 1};
        
        Arrays.sort(numbers, Collections.reverseOrder());
        
        System.out.println("Sorted numbers in decreasing order: " + Arrays.toString(numbers));

    }
}
```

In this program, we first declare an array of Integers. Then we use the sort() method from the Arrays class to sort the array. We use the reverseOrder() function from the Collections class as a comparator to sort the array in decreasing order. Finally, we print the sorted array.

Please note that it is important to use the Integer array instead of int array because Collections.reverseOrder() function and Arrays.sort() method work with objects, not with primitive types.

When this program runs, it will print:

```console
Sorted numbers in decreasing order: [8, 6, 3, 2, 1]
```
