can you make this code c-compliant?
def average_in_interval(l: list, lower_limit: int, upper_limit: int) -> bool:
    mean = sum(l) / len(l)
    return lower_limit <= mean <= upper_limit
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Yes, here is an equivalent C compliant code to the Python one provided:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

double listAverage(int list[], int size) {
    int sum = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
        sum += list[i];
    }
    return (double)sum / (double)size;
}

int isInRange(int list[], int size, int lower_limit, int upper_limit) {
    double avg = listAverage(list, size);
    return lower_limit <= avg && avg <= upper_limit;
}
```
<|end|>


