Develop a secure API endpoint using Python, FastAPI and SQLAlchemy that utilizes JWT token authentication and OAuth2. The API should be able to handle CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on user data that is stored in an SQL database. The user data should include but not be limited to information such as username, hashed password and user roles (admin, user, guest). Implement throttling to limit the number of API requests per minute for each user. An extra challenge would be handling connection pool exhaustion in case of a large number of concurrent requests.
