Also, what's the formula to convert angles expressed in radians to degrees and back again?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
To convert an angle from degrees to radians, use the formula: 

radians = degrees * (π/180)

To convert an angle from radians to degrees, use the formula:

degrees = radians * (180/π)

Just remember, Pi radians is the equivalent of 180 degrees, and use this relationship to convert between the two.
