```

In this code, the `median` function from the statistics library is used to calculate the median of the values. After that, the `median_absolute_deviation` function from the scipy stats module is used to calculate the median absolute deviation from the median. Please ensure that you have `scipy` package installed in your environment to use `median_absolute_deviation`.

Please note that 'statistics' library only provides basic statistical functions while 'scipy' provides advanced statistical functions.

**Note:** The `stats.median_absolute_deviation()` in the 'Scipy' library will be depracated in release 1.7.0. So, instead of it, you can use `stats.median_abs_deviation()` from the same library.
