Construct a method in C# programming language that not only accepts an integer as an argument and returns the leftmost digit, but also checks and handles exceptions when the input is non-integer. Ensure efficiency in handling large integers.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a method in C# programming language that meets your requirements:

```C#
public int GetLeftmostDigit(string input)
{
    // Check if the input is an integer
    if (!Int64.TryParse(input, out long num))
    {
        throw new ArgumentException("Input must be an integer");
    }

    // Convert the number to absolute to handle negative numbers
    num = Math.Abs(num);

    // Get the leftmost digit
    while (num >= 10)
    {
        num /= 10;
    }

    return (int)num;
}
```

In this method, the argument is expected to be a string, this way we can use the `TryParse` method for the `Int64` class which can check if the string can be converted to a number. If it can't, it returns false and we throw an `ArgumentException`.

The loop keeps dividing the number by 10 until it's a single digit number, this way we get the leftmost digit. This method should work fine for very large numbers as it uses `Int64` to store the integer.

To use the method:

```C#
try
{
    Console.WriteLine(GetLeftmostDigit("1234567890")); // Outputs: 1
    Console.WriteLine(GetLeftmostDigit("-1234567890")); // Outputs: 1
    Console.WriteLine(GetLeftmostDigit("abc")); // Throws an exception
}
catch (ArgumentException ex)
{
    Console.WriteLine(ex.Message); // Outputs: Input must be an integer
}
```
Please note it's good practice to validate all inputs, hence we validate by using TryParse method from Int64. This will ensure that the program does not throw a runtime exception when provided with invalid input (anything non-numeric). If TryParse method can't parse the input into an Int64, it returns false and in that case, we throw an argument exception with a proper error message that the input should be numeric. Additionally, if the number entered has negative sign, then it is taken care of by converting the absolute value of the entered number.
<|end|>


