Generate a complex password of 10 characters which must include at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one digit, one special symbol, and one non-english letter.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a Python solution using the random and string libraries:

```python
import random
import string

# Define the different character types we will use
lowers = string.ascii_lowercase
uppers = string.ascii_uppercase
digits = string.digits
specials = string.punctuation
non_english = 'ÆÐƎƏƐƔĲŊŒẞØǷȜǼǽ'

# Generate one character of each type
password = [
    random.choice(lowers),
    random.choice(uppers),
    random.choice(digits),
    random.choice(specials),
    random.choice(non_english),
]

# Add additional random characters until we reach 10
while len(password) < 10:
    password.append(random.choice(lowers + uppers + digits + specials + non_english))

# Shuffle the characters around so the password isn't predictable
random.shuffle(password)

# Join the characters into a string and print the password
password = ''.join(password)
print(password)
```

This code generates a random character from each category (lowercase, uppercase, digit, special, non-english) to ensure the password contains at least one of each. It then adds random characters from any category until the password is 10 characters long. Finally, it shuffles the characters so that the order isn't predictable according to how they were added.

Keep in mind that not every system or service will accept all special characters or non-English characters. Please adjust the "specials" and "non_english" strings as necessary to fit within the allowed character set for wherever this password is being used.
<|end|>


