I'm writing app that should manage clients that connected to hotspot. I'm tried find some info about "how to disconnect users from hotspot android" but i found nothing. (api 29)
Can somebody help me, please?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
In Android, starting from API 29, access to relevant API for WiFi management has been limited or removed, therefore there is no official APIs to manage the hotspot in the same way it was done in previous versions.

You won't be able to directly disconnect a client when they're connected to Hotspot due to Android security restrictions. However, there is a workaround to achieve this - you can turn off the hotspot and turn it back on. When you do this, all users will be disconnected. But this method will disconnect all users, not any specific one.

If you need to manage hotspot clients programmatically, you may need to use a rooted device with a custom API.

Remember, manipulating WiFi and networks is sensitive and many methods are either deprecated or hidden on Android devices specifically due to security and privacy reasons.

As a note, it is also significant to consider the ethical implications and legal liabilities of manipulating a client's connection to a hotspot without clear permission or notification. It may be seen as invasions of privacy if done without clear understanding and consent from the parties involved.
<|end|>


