Design a program in Java to sort a given array of integers in ascending order.
[5, 8, 2, 4, 10, 1, 7]
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a simple solution in Java using the bubble sort algorithm:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String args[]) {

        // Our initial unsorted array
        int array[] ={5,8,2,4,10,1,7};

        // Begin by printing the original array
        System.out.println("Array Before Bubble Sort");
        for(int i=0; i < array.length; i++){
            System.out.print(array[i] + " ");
        }
        System.out.println();
        
        // Perform the bubble sort
        bubbleSort(array);

        // Print the final sorted array
        System.out.println("Array After Bubble Sort");
        for(int i=0; i < array.length; i++){
            System.out.print(array[i] + " ");
        }

    }
    
    static void bubbleSort(int[] array) {
        int n = array.length;
        int temp = 0;
        for(int i=0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j=1; j < (n-i); j++){
                
                // Swap the elements if needed
                if(array[j-1] > array[j]){
                    temp = array[j-1];
                    array[j-1] = array[j];
                    array[j] = temp;
                }
                
            }
        }
    }
}
```

This program begins by printing the initial unsorted array. It then conducts a bubble sort on the array. This type of sort repeatedly steps through the list, compares adjacent elements and swaps them if they are in the wrong order. The pass through the list is repeated until the list is sorted. After the array is sorted, it is printed again to show the final sorted array.

Note that this is not the most efficient sorting algorithm (especially for large lists), but it is simple and serves well for illustrative purposes. For more efficiency, you may want to use other sorting algorithms, such as quicksort, mergesort, heapsort, etc., or you could use the built-in sorting function in the Java Arrays class, Arrays.sort().
<|end|>


