Construct a Java program that prompts the user to input a numeric value and then determine and display the corresponding Fibonacci number in the sequence.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a simple Java program that takes a numeric value as input and displays the corresponding Fibonacci number in the sequence:

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Fibonacci {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter a numeric value:");
        int n = scanner.nextInt();
        int result = fibonacci(n);
        System.out.println("The corresponding Fibonacci number is: " + result);
    }

    private static int fibonacci(int n) {
        if (n <= 1) {
            return n;
        } else {
            return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
        }
    }
}
```

To run this program, copy and paste this code into a file named `Fibonacci.java` on your computer. Make sure that you have the Java Development Kit (JDK) installed. Open a terminal (or command prompt) and navigate to the directory containing the file. Then, run the following commands:

```sh
$ javac Fibonacci.java # this will compile the code
$ java Fibonacci       # this will run the program
```

After running the java Fibonacci command, you will be prompted to enter a numeric value. Enter your desired input, and the program will display the corresponding Fibonacci number in the sequence.
<|end|>


