Develop a function for array manipulation with a specific emphasis on sending the numerical values of the array into a state of ascending order.
[3, 1, 9, 5, 4]
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here's a simple Python function to solve the problem:

```python
def array_sort(arr):
    return sorted(arr)

array = [3, 1, 9, 5, 4]
sorted_array = array_sort(array)
print(sorted_array)
```
When you run this code, it will print:

[1, 3, 4, 5, 9]

This function uses the built-in `sorted()` function in Python which sorts an iterable and returns a new sorted list from the elements of any iterable.

If you want to do it in place (i.e., sort the array without creating a new one), you can use `list.sort()`, as follows:

```python
def array_sort_in_place(arr):
    arr.sort()
    return arr

array = [3, 1, 9, 5, 4]
sorted_array = array_sort_in_place(array)
print(sorted_array)
```
This will also print:

[1, 3, 4, 5, 9]
