No, the way to toggle case-sensitivity in `less` is indeed by using the `-i` command line option when starting `less`. However, for the active session you can use `-i` option as well. 

1. Press `-`(minus/dash) key
2. Type `i` key
3. Press enter.

This will allow you to toggle case-insensitive searches in the currently running `less` session. Do remember that this is a toggle, so running it again will make the searches case-sensitive once more.
<|end|>


