Here is a simple JavaScript function that converts a number into binary format:

```
function toBinary(number) {
  return (number >>> 0).toString(2);
}
```

This function works by using the ">>>" operator, also known as zero fill right shift operator, to ensure the number is an unsigned integer (needed for negative numbers). It then uses the `toString()` method to convert the number to a binary string. The argument 2 is passed into the `toString()` method to specify the base-2 numeral system.
