```JavaScript
var productSearch = document.getElementById('productSearch');
var productList = document.getElementById('productList');

const products = [
  {name: "iPhone", price: 499},
  {name: "MacBook Pro", price: 1499},
  {name: "iPad Pro", price: 799},
];

function renderProducts() {
  productList.innerHTML = '';
  products.forEach(function(product) {
    var li = document.createElement('li');
    li.innerText = product.name + ' - ' + '$' + product.price;
    productList.appendChild(li);
  });
}

function searchProduct() {
  var searchQuery = productSearch.value.toLowerCase();
  var searchedProducts = products.filter(function(product) {
    return product.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchQuery);
  });
  products = searchedProducts;
  renderProducts();
}

renderProducts();
```

This code constructs a simple product search functionality where a user can input text and the list will be filtered and re-rendered to show only those products whose names match the input. 

Please note that this code should be properly embedded within HTML, CSS, and JS files, and they should be properly linked together. Also, please note the restriction that it's a case-insensitive search and doesn't handle empty strings or additional spaces. Make sure to enhance the functionality as needed.
