<|asst|>
Yes, the code can be translated to PHP. The PHP version of the code will look like this.

```php
<?php
function is_prime($n) {
    // 1 is not a prime number
    if($n == 1) {
        return false;
    }

    // 2 and 3 are prime numbers
    if($n < 4) {
        return true;
    }
    
    // except 2 all other even numbers are not prime
    if($n % 2 == 0) {
        return false;
    }
    
    // check for factors up to the square root of n
    for($i = 3; $i <= intval(sqrt($n)) + 1; $i += 2) {
        if($n % $i == 0) {
            return false;
        }
    }

    return true;
}
?>
```
