After installing a third-party SDK, it very discourteously makes one if its templates the default item in "Add New Item..." dialog in Visual Studio 2005. This is also the case for all other similar dialogs - "Add Class...", "Add User Control..." etc.

Is there a way to change this behavior?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Unfortunately, there isn't a built-in way to change which item is selected by default in the "Add New Item..." dialog in Visual Studio 2005.

You can change the order of the templates by renaming the .zip files in the ProjectTemplates and/or ItemTemplates folder under the Visual Studio install directory (usually something like "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio 8\Common7\IDE\") - the templates are displayed in alphabetical order.

But, there isn't a way to change that the first template will always be selected by default. This is a functionality limitation in Visual Studio 2005 and older versions.

If you find this a persistent nuisance — and you don't need the third-party SDK template that's inserting itself at the top of the list — you could try deleting its .zip file from ProjectTemplates or ItemTemplates directory. However, before doing this, make sure that this doesn't affect the use of the SDK and remember to backup the .zip file.

Starting with Visual Studio 2010 and newer, Visual Studio remembers the last item you selected in the "Add New Item..." dialog and selects it by default the next time you open it. This feature greatly improves this behavior. If you're able, I'd recommend looking into upgrading for this and many other improvements.
<|end|>


