I need to send MMS thought a C# application. I have already found 2 interesting components:
[http://www.winwap.com](http://www.winwap.com)
[http://www.nowsms.com](http://www.nowsms.com)

Does anyone have experience with other third party components?
Could someone explain what kind of server I need to send those MMS? Is it a classic SMTP Server?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
MMS (Multimedia Messaging Service) is not, strictly speaking, the same as email hence it does not use SMTP - it is a system used to send multimedia content in a manner similar to SMS and typically used on mobile devices. Therefore, to send MMS from a C# application, you would generally use a gateway service that provides an API which your application will communicate with.

For instance, NowSMS provides an HTTP interface for sending MMS, where you post a specially-constructed HTTP request to their gateway server, and it takes care of the rest.

WinWap seems to offer an SDK that presumably offers a high-level interface that hides some of these details.

As an alternative, you might consider:
 - [Twilio](https://www.twilio.com/mms): Provides MMS services with a very developer-friendly API that you can use in C#. They have detailed documentation and SDKs that can help get you started.
 - [Plivo](https://www.plivo.com/sms-api/mms/): Similar service to Twilio.
 - [Nexmo](https://developer.nexmo.com/messages/code-snippets/mms/send-photo)

Before choosing a provider, make sure to review their pricing options, API support, and any other factors important to your project, such as support for specific mobile operators or countries.

Make sure also to abide by all relevant laws when sending MMS messages from your application. MMS can easily be seen as invasive and be subjected to very strict marketing laws in many countries.
<|end|>


