I'm trying to make it so that if the user has a `ValueKey` folder. and the name of the currency is `ValueKey`

local badges = game:GetService("BadgeService")
local badgeId  = 2130265816
local players = game:GetService("Players")

players.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)
    local value = players.ValueKey.ValueKey
    value.Value.Changed:Connect(function(newVal)
        if newVal == 100 then --award badge for 100 candies
            --badges:AwardBadge(player.UserId, badgeId)
            print('you received a badge')
        end
    end)
end)


But for some reason the text does not want to be displayed in the console, I can’t understand why at least the value has the number 100 or more
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Your code seems to be trying to get the `ValueKey` from the `Players`service, not from the individual `Player` who has been added to the game.

You can take the `player` parameter from `PlayerAdded` event and use it to get the currency `ValueKey` for each player.

Here is the correct code:

```lua
local badges = game:GetService("BadgeService")
local badgeId  = 2130265816
local players = game:GetService("Players")

players.PlayerAdded:Connect(function(player)
    -- Get the player's ValueKey (Make sure that the ValueKey is a direct child of the player)
    local value = player:FindFirstChild("ValueKey")

    if value then
        -- Connect the Value's Changed event
        value.Changed:Connect(function(newVal)
            if newVal == 100 then --award badge for 100 candies
                --badges:AwardBadge(player.UserId, badgeId)
                print('you received a badge')
            end
        end)
    else
        warn("No ValueKey found for player "..player.Name)
    end
end)
```

The above code should work as you expect. It will search for `ValueKey` under each new player and listen for changes on it. When the value changes, it will award the player a badge when the value is 100 or more. If `ValueKey` is not found as a direct child of the player, it will display a warning in the output.

Just make sure to replace `print('you received a badge')` with `badges:AwardBadge(player.UserId, badgeId)` to actually award the badges.
