HTML:
```html
<div id="wrapper">
  <div id="content" style="float: right;"></div>
  <div id="additional" style="float: left;"></div>
</div>
```

CSS:
```css
#wrapper {
  width: 100%; 
  height: 100%;
}

#content {
  background: red;
  width: 40%;
  float: right; 
}

#additional {
  background: blue;
  width: 40%;
  float: left; 
}
```

In your analysis, be sure to consider the following factors: 
- How the HTML and CSS codes are structured.
- The possible inheritances in the CSS code.
- Interactions between different elements and styles.
- Side effects of CSS properties.
- Responsive design considerations.
