```javascript
// Time variable in seconds
var time = 10;

// Function that runs the countdown
function countdownTimer() {
  var timer = setInterval(function () {
    document.getElementById('timer').innerHTML = time;
    time--;
    if (time < 0) {
      clearInterval(timer);
      // Redirect to the desired webpage
      window.location.href = "http://new-domain.com";
    }
  }, 1000);
}

// Run the countdown as soon as the window loads
window.onload = countdownTimer;
```

Explanation: The CSS styles the pop-up window. The JavaScript section starts a countdown as soon as the browser window has fully loaded, and every second, it reduces the timer (initially set to 10 seconds) by one. When the countdown reaches 0, it will redirect the user to a new webpage.

Remember, automatic redirection may not be a good user experience and might confuse some users. Therefore, you should make sure users know what is happening and how they can opt out if necessary.

Also, since this is a client-side JavaScript, users may prevent the redirection (e.g., by disabling JavaScript) if they wish to do so.
