Please devise a Python method that surveils a fictitious banking account's equilibrium. The operating principle is as such: it consumes an array of integers or floating-point digits meant to either represent deposit proceedings (+ve figures) or withdrawal actions (-ve figures). The method halts and proclaims True as soon the equilibrium inclines beneath zero; on the contrary, it emits False.

You are further charged to integrate a handling module for floating-point digits, such module can be activated or deactivated using a logical argument. It is expected of you to utilize List and Union from the typing module for applying annotation protocols.

