I use Gmail Workplace and am trying to understand and setup SPF at my webb host (not Google). Should I setup a gmail SPF or an SPF for my own IP adress to avoid having mails sent via php on my server, but with gmail SMTP, marked as spam?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
SPF (Sender Policy Framework) is an email authentication method designed to detect forging sender addresses during delivery of the email. In your case, since you are sending emails via Google's SMTP server, you need to add Google's SPF record in your DNS SPF record.

Google's SPF is: `v=spf1 include:_spf.google.com ~all`

You need to add this in your domain DNS record. 

However, make sure if you are using other services to send email from your domain you also include them in your SPF record. Multiple SPF records are not recommended for one domain, hence try to keep all your services sending emails in one SPF record.

Example:
`v=spf1 ip4:xxx.xxx.xx.xx include:_spf.google.com ~all`

Where `ip4:xxx.xxx.xx.xx` is the IP of your own server (if it sends out mail) and `_spf.google.com` is Google's SPF. 

Note: before doing any changes make sure you know the risks if you misconfigure the SPF since it may lead to your email being marked as spam.
<|end|>


