Code a solution that prints out the string "Hello, [name]!" and calculate the length of the resulting string using string interpolation in JavaScript. Additionally, fix the issues with the given erroneous code below:

```javascript
function greet(name) {
  let greeting = `Hello, $name!`;
  console.log(greeting);
};

greet('John');
```

What will be the length of the resulting string after the code has been corrected?
