Design and implement a dynamic HTML form with the following requirements:

1. The form should have six fields: Name, Email, Phone Number, Address, Upload a Profile Picture and a Multi-Select Field for Hobbies.
2. Implement JavaScript validation for each field:
    - The Name field should not accept numeric values. Also, it should not be empty.
    - For the Email field, check if it's in a valid email format and it should not be empty.
    - The Phone Number field should only accept numeric values and should meet a given pattern of a phone number (you can select any regional pattern).
    - The Address field should not be empty and should have a minimum number of characters.
    - For the Profile Picture upload function, ensure the uploaded file is an image file format, with a certain maximum size limit.
    - For the Multi-Select Field, ensure at least two options are selected.
3. Use AJAX to submit form data and send a request to a server without reloading the page. 
4. Once the data is validated, the user's inputs should be stored in a local database.
5. Display a 'Thank you' message along with the user's name and the uploaded profile picture after the submission is completed successfully.

The code must include suitable comments and should follow the best practices in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
This problem involves several aspects of web development, including HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and AJAX.

Due to the formatting limitations of the text-based response, I will only provide the skeleton code necessary for this task. In practical conditions, you should have some server-side code waiting to handle the AJAX POST request and a local database to store user data.

Here is the code:

HTML form with all fields specified:

```html
<form id="myForm" enctype="multipart/form-data">
    <input id="name" name="name" type="text" placeholder="Name"/>
    <input id="email" name="email" type="email" placeholder="Email"/>
    <input id="phoneNumber" name="phoneNumber" type="text" placeholder="Phone Number"/>
    <textarea id="address" name="address" placeholder="Address"></textarea>
    <input id="profilePic" name="profilePic" type="file">
    <select id="hobbies" name="hobbies" multiple>
        <option value="hobby1">Hobby 1</option>
        <option value="hobby2">Hobby 2</option>
        <option value="hobby3">Hobby 3</option>
        <!-- Other options can be added similarly -->
    </select>
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

JavaScript validation with AJAX form submission:

```javascript
$(document).ready(function(){
    $('#myForm').submit(function(e){
        e.preventDefault();

        let name = $('#name').val().trim();
        if(!name || /\d/.test(name)){
            alert('Invalid Name!');
            return false;
        }
        
        let email = $('#email').val().trim();
        if(!email || !/.+@.+\..+/.test(email)){
            alert('Invalid Email!');
            return false;
        }
        
        let phoneNumber = $('#phoneNumber').val().trim();
        if(!phoneNumber || !/^\d{3}-\d{3}-\d{4}$/.test(phoneNumber)){ //format: 123-456-7890
            alert('Invalid Phone Number!');
            return false;
        }
        
        let address = $('#address').val().trim();
        if(!address || address.length < 5){
            alert('Invalid Address!');
            return false;
        }

        let profilePic = $('#profilePic').get(0).files[0];
        if(!profilePic || !/image\/.*/.test(profilePic.type) || profilePic.size > 2 * 1024 * 1024){
            alert('Invalid Profile Picture!');
            return false;
        }
        
        let hobbies = $('#hobbies').val();
        if(!hobbies || hobbies.length < 2){
            alert('Select at least two hobbies!');
            return false;
        }
        
        // AJAX data submission
        let formData = new FormData(this);
        $.ajax({
            type: 'POST',
            url: '/submitForm', // server-side script
            data: formData,
            processData: false,
            contentType: false,
            success: function(response){
                $('#myForm').hide();
                $('body').append(
                    '<p>Thank you, ' + name + '!</p>',
                    '<img src="' + URL.createObjectURL(profilePic) + '"/>'
                );
            }
        });
    });
});
```

This code is written using basics of HTML, CSS and jQuery library is used for AJAX call. Form data is appended to FormData and the object is then passed to $.ajax.
<|end|>


