Suppose I have an existing FX Swap, suppose the spot leg is already settled, so only forward leg is left.
Question: What will be the P&L for this instrument - only forward leg NPV or spot leg is also marked-to-market to current spot rate?
Thanks a lot!
<|end|>
<|asst|>
The P&L for this instrument will only be the NPV of the forward leg. Once the spot leg is settled, it no longer impacts the valuation of the FX swap as the cashflow has already occurred. Therefore, only the NPV of the forward leg which is yet to be settled will affect the P&L, and yes it would be marked-to-market using the current forward rate. The spot rate at present would not impact the valuation of an existing forward leg.
<|end|>


