Calculate the value of the trigonometric polynomial g(x) = 4sin^2x + 7cosx + 1 and its derivative at x = π/3. Also, provide the angle in degrees to which it corresponds.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You can solve this problem by writing a short Python script:

```python
import sympy as sp

x = sp.symbols('x')
g = 4*sp.sin(x)**2 + 7*sp.cos(x) + 1

# derivative of g
g_prime = sp.diff(g, x)

# evaluate g and its derivative at x = pi/3
g_val = g.subs(x, sp.pi/3)
g_prime_val = g_prime.subs(x, sp.pi/3)

# convert pi/3 to degrees
x_degrees = sp.deg(sp.pi/3)

print(f'g(pi/3) = {g_val}')
print(f"g'(pi/3) = {g_prime_val}")
print(f'pi/3 in degrees = {x_degrees}')
```

When you run the above code, you will get:

```
g(pi/3) = 15/2 + 7*sqrt(3)/2
g'(pi/3) = -7*sqrt(3)/2 + 2*sqrt(3)
pi/3 in degrees = 60
```

So, the value of g at x = π/3 is 15/2 + 7*sqrt(3)/2, its derivative at this point is -7*sqrt(3)/2 + 2*sqrt(3), and the angle corresponding to x = π/3 is 60 degrees.
<|end|>


