Develop a Python function that determines whether the quantity of divisors for a specified number is even, compiles an array of these divisors, calculates the sum of these divisors, and identifies the highest prime number among the divisors. The function must be designed to manage edge cases such as negative integers, zero, non-integer inputs, complex numbers, quaternion numbers, and now also octonion numbers.

In addition to the above, the function should also have the capacity to distinguish and return the least common multiple (LCM) and the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the divisors. If the LCM or GCD cannot be determined, the function should return a suitable message. 

