I have a method that periodically (e.g. once in every 10 secs) try to connect to a server and read some data from it. The server might not be available all the time. If the server is not available the method throws an exception.

What would be the best way to implement a wrapper method that doesn't throw an exception except if the server wasn't available for at least one minute?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
One way to do this would be to use exception handling in combination with a timer. Here is a simple Python implementation with comments for explanation:

```python
import time

def connect_to_server():
    '''
    Your original method that connects to a server and reads data.
    May throw exception if server is not available.
    '''
    pass

def wrapper():
    # Record the time of the first failed attempt
    first_fail_time = None

    while True:
        try:
            connect_to_server()    # Try connecting to server
            first_fail_time = None # Reset first_fail_time if the connection is successful

        except Exception:          # Catch an exception if the server is not available
            if first_fail_time is None:
                first_fail_time = time.time()       # Record the time of the first failed attempt

            elif time.time() - first_fail_time >= 60:   # If the server has been unavailable for 60 seconds
                raise Exception('Server has been unavailable for 60 seconds')  # Throw an exception

        time.sleep(10)   # Wait for 10 seconds before trying again

wrapper()
```

This wrapper method keeps trying to connect to the server. If a connection fails, it keeps track of the time of the first failed attempt. If the server remains unavailable for 60 seconds, it throws an exception. 

Please note, the actual exception and error handling logic should be more sophisticated which precisely catches the connection failures and also differentiates between different kinds of exceptions.

Also, this approach can cause an infinite loop if not properly managed. It will continue to try to connect to the server indefinitely unless a connection is made or the one minute timeout exception is raised. This should be refined to fit specific requirements.

Remember to replace `connect_to_server` with your original method.
<|end|>


