When I try to post to Medium.com following their documention, I get this error:

requests.exceptions.JSONDecodeError: Expecting value: line 1 column 1 (char 0)


To be specific I am only trying to use the create_post function that the client provides.
Has anyone faced this error before? And how did you fix it? Any help would be greatly appreciated.
I followed the instructions in their documentation and this error was not included in their expected auth errors
<|end|>
<|asst|>
The JSONDecodeError typically arises when you're trying to parse an empty document. In the context of using requests in Python, you're probably receiving an empty document (or no document at all) in the response to your HTTP request to Medium.com API.

Make sure:
1. The API endpoint is correctly defined & there's no issue with the endpoint you're sending a request to.
2. The request object is correctly structured with all necessary headers & body.

The error message suggests that the JSON decoder is unable to find a value at line 1 column 1, so that indicates that there is likely nothing to parse (either your JSON object is empty, or it is non-existent).

To debug this:
1. Print out the raw response (Before decoding it as JSON) & see what its content is using `response.text`. This will give you the raw text of the response from server, you might be getting an HTML response, an error message, etc.
2. Also, check the HTTP status code of the response using `response.status_code` to check if the request was successful.

If you're able to see valid JSON in the response and status code is 200, there might be an issue with the JSON library you're using. You might want to try updating the library or try using an alternative method/library to parse the JSON.

Furthermore, check if you're using API key correctly (if required) and you have sufficient access rights or tokens got expired. If everything looks good, it might be an issue with the Medium API itself and you might need to contact Medium's support for the same.
<|end|>


