Develop a JavaScript function that, when provided with a specific input string, will analyze and return the lengthiest palindromic substring present within it.
"abacdaaadccb"
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a JavaScript function that uses Dynamic Programming approach to detect the longest palindic substring in a given string.

```javascript
function longestPalindrome(inputString) {
  let len = inputString.length;
  let dp = Array(len).fill(null).map(() => Array(len).fill(false));
  let longestPal = '';

  for (let l = 0; l < len; l++) {
    for (let i = 0; i + l < len; i++) {
      let j = i + l;

      if (l === 0) {
        dp[i][j] = true; 
      } else if (l === 1 && inputString[i] === inputString[j]) {
        dp[i][j] = true;
      } else if (inputString[i] === inputString[j] && dp[i+1][j-1]) {
        dp[i][j] = true;
      }

      if (dp[i][j] && l + 1 > longestPal.length) {
        longestPal = inputString.substring(i, j + 1);
      }
    }
  }

  return longestPal;
}

console.log(longestPalindrome('abacdaaadccb'));
```
The function `longestPalindrome` dynamically calculates whether substrings at different lengths are palindromic. By filling up the dynamic programming table from smaller substrings to larger ones, it ensures the calculation of each substring relies only on the palindrome information of its smaller substrings, which avoids redundant computation.

Finally, it extracts and returns the longest palindromic substring. For the example provided, it returns 'aaa'.
<|end|>


